lts of the RAM Legacy Stock Assessment Database: https://www.ramlegacy.org/\n\nThis aggregated data was provided by Michael Melnychuk, researcher on the RAM Legacy Database.\n\nThese results were published in PNAS here:\nHilborn, R., Amoroso, R. O., Anderson, C. M., Baum, J. K., Branch, T. A., Costello, C., ... & Ye, Y. (2020). Effective fisheries management instrumental in improving fish stock status. Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, 117(4), 2218-2224. Available at: https://www.pnas.org/content/117/4/2218\n\nDefinitions are as follows:\n– 'Biomass' is a measure of biomass of fish divided by the biomass of fish at the maximum sustainable yield (B / Bmsy)\n– 'Fishing pressure' is a measure of fishing pressure divided by the pressure at the maximum sustainable yield (U / Umsy)\n– 'Catch' is a measure of the annual catch divided by the mean catch across the stock's time series"}}},"entityKey":{"225490":{"name":"Tuna","code":null},"227283":{"name":"Bivalves and gastropods","code":null},"227284":{"name":"Mackerels","code":null},"227285":{"name":"Cephalopods (e.g. octopus, squid)","code":null},"227286":{"name":"Crabs and lobsters","code":null},"227287":{"name":"Elasmobranchs","code":null},"227288":{"name":"Forage fish","code":null},"227289":{"name":"Gadids","code":null},"227290":{"name":"Other marine fish","code":null},"227291":{"name":"Other marine percoidids","code":null},"227292":{"name":"Other scorpaenids","code":null},"227293":{"name":"Pleuronectids","code":null},"227294":{"name":"Sebastids","code":null},"227295":{"name":"Shrimps","code":null}}}